-- Turkish Banks' Profit Rose 14% in Year to May, Outpacing Deposit Growth
-- Ali Berat Meric
-- 2010-07-02T08:35:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-02/turkish-banks-profit-rose-14-in-year-to-may-outpacing-deposit-growth.html

          
          
             Profit in Turkey’s banking industry
grew 14 percent in the first five months from a year ago, the
regulator said.  
 Net income in the year to May was 10.3 billion liras ($6.5
billion), according to preliminary figures, a spokesman for the
 Banking Regulation and Supervision Agency  in Ankara said,
speaking on the usual condition of anonymity.  
 Loans rose 12 percent from the end of 2009 to 439 billion
liras and non-performing lending declined 1.9 percent to 21.4
billion liras over the same period, the regulator said. Deposits
gained 5.2 percent from the year-end to 541.2 billion liras  
 Banks’ capital adequacy ratio fell to 19.3 percent in May
from 20.6 percent in December and 19.5 percent in May 2009, the
regulator said.  
